1945;;Madonna of the Seven Moons;;British;;Arthur Crabtree;;Phyllis Calvert, Stewart Granger, Patricia Roc;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madonna_of_the_Seven_Moons;;A buried trauma from the past holds the key to the disappearance of a respectable married woman. Maddalena has a dual personality which leads her to forsake her husband and daughter, to flee to the house of the Seven Moons in Florence as the mistress of a jewel thief.[5]